title: Luden
description: Huizinga makes it clear in the foreword of his book that he means the play element of culture, and not the play element in culture. He writes that he titled the initial lecture the book is based on The Play Element of Culture. This title was repeatedly corrected to in Culture, a revision he objected to. The English version modified the subtitle of the book to A Study of the Play-Element in Culture, contradicting Huizinga's stated intention. The translator explains in a footnote in the Foreword, Logically, of course, Huizinga is correct; but as English prepositions are not governed by logic I have retained the more euphonious ablative in this sub-title.

I'm gonna get my engineers to invent a combustible lemon that burns your house down!
